00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:49.759
to think out of the box ideas. A lot of young
people in colleges saw the video and this

00:23:49.759 --> 00:23:53.019
became number one on MTV they see.

00:23:53.019 --> 00:24:00.129
And so it gets -- just like movies and books,
music and music video allows us this sort

00:24:00.129 --> 00:24:02.070
of platform to start a dialog.

00:24:02.070 --> 00:24:08.610
I want to give you another short example of
that. During the summer, the greatest single

00:24:08.610 --> 00:24:16.070
natural disaster on the face of the planet
was the floods in Pakistan. And it was bigger

00:24:16.070 --> 00:24:23.399
than Haiti, tsunami, and the Kashmir earthquake
put together, yet it got zero coverage, very

00:24:23.399 --> 00:24:28.049
little coverage in the global media.

00:24:28.049 --> 00:24:37.100
So I thought, "What can I do?" I mean, and
I looked at the tools that we have today,

00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:43.029
Facebook, Twitter, email, and I sent out this
sort of mass email to all the people that

00:24:43.029 --> 00:24:47.659
I knew saying, "Look this is happening. It's
not being covered in the media. What can we

00:24:47.659 --> 00:24:48.659
do about it?"

