00:33:55.990 --> 00:34:01.629
Foundation. So there were American teachers
teaching in Lahore, Karachi, Islamabad and

00:34:01.629 --> 00:34:11.940
it was a much more outward looking culture;
but a very strong home grown culture as well.

00:34:11.940 --> 00:34:16.250
But rock music and all that was available
when I was very young. I didn't know that

00:34:16.250 --> 00:34:23.110
much at that time, but in the 80s there was
a military dictatorship and a military dictator

00:34:23.110 --> 00:34:32.230
by the name of General Zia came and although
he was fighting the Soviets in Afghanistan

00:34:32.230 --> 00:34:37.760
those 11 years of military dictatorship completely
took the cultural vision of that country into

00:34:37.760 --> 00:34:38.760
another age.

00:34:38.760 --> 00:34:46.980
I write about that in great length. It was
very isolated. There wasn't really a cultural

00:34:46.980 --> 00:34:53.240
vision. I mean all the culture he thought
that was permissible was basically the holy

00:34:53.240 --> 00:34:55.530
book, the Koran, and that's it.

00:34:55.530 --> 00:35:03.370
