00:35:35.600 --> 00:35:45.950
It's this, a beautiful ethereal place in South
Asia where since partition of India into Pakistan

00:35:45.950 --> 00:35:52.340
and India, there's always been sort of this
conflict.

00:35:52.340 --> 00:35:58.280
And when we went for the first time -- our
bend toured India for the first time in '98

00:35:58.280 --> 00:36:02.950
 -- we got so many emails from Kashmir, from
Srinagar of teenagers wanting us to go and

00:36:02.950 --> 00:36:08.970
perform there. And I asked the promoter, we
were doing a tour all across India, can we

00:36:08.970 --> 00:36:16.040
go up and do a gig in Srinagar? So he looked
at me; he said, "Uh okay. Don't let your idealism

00:36:16.040 --> 00:36:21.620
make you run off a cliff. It's never gonna
happen in this lifetime," he said. And this

00:36:21.620 --> 00:36:25.990
is '98 when he said that. And I said, "You
know what? We'll see about that."

00:36:25.990 --> 00:36:34.650
But it took 10 years. Ten years later we got
an opportunity from the South Asian Foundation,

00:36:34.650 --> 00:36:41.370
again arts and culture based non-profit which
said, "Look we wanna start building bridges

00:36:41.370 --> 00:36:45.090
and we think music is the best way to move
forward and especially the kind of music you

00:36:45.090 --> 00:36:49.580
guys play. So will you come and perform?"
And I was a non-brainer. I said, "Yes."

00:36:49.580 --> 00:36:56.370
But as soon as that got published in the news
in India and Pakistan, I started getting death

00:36:56.370 --> 00:37:01.400
threats from militants. They said, "If you
land in Srinagar, you will be shot on sight."

00:37:01.400 --> 00:37:07.070
So I kept that information from the rest of
the band. [laughs]

00:37:07.070 --> 00:37:08.070
[laughter]

00:37:08.070 --> 00:37:14.001
I said, "Yeah, look it's gonna be great. It's
May, it's gonna be beautiful. We're playing

00:37:14.001 --> 00:37:20.220
at this place called the Dal Lake." Anybody
been to Srinagar out there?

00:37:20.220 --> 00:37:25.480
So let me describe this place to you. It's
a beautiful lake surrounded by the Himalayan

00:37:25.480 --> 00:37:33.400
Mountains where legend has it that Ravi Shankar
gave George Harrison his first sitar lesson.

00:37:33.400 --> 00:37:34.400
[laughter]

00:37:34.400 --> 00:37:36.220
And that's where our stage was gonna be.

00:37:36.220 --> 00:37:38.440
So I said, "It's worth dying [laughs]

00:37:38.440 --> 00:37:39.440
[laughter]

00:37:39.440 --> 00:37:41.580
to do this gig." [laughs]

00:37:41.580 --> 00:37:42.580
[laughter]

00:37:42.580 --> 00:37:49.740
And we landed in Srinagar and we got off from
the airport to the hotel in four bullet proof

00:37:49.740 --> 00:37:56.600
Jeeps. And they were driving at 100 miles
per hour and there was like this sort of the

00:37:56.600 --> 00:37:58.070
whole city was under siege.

00:37:58.070 --> 00:38:04.890
And what had happened was college students
who wanted to come were prevented from coming

00:38:04.890 --> 00:38:11.280
by this barbed wire all around the place.
And until the day of the show, we didn't know

00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:15.570
if the show was gonna happen. But an amazing
thing happened and I tell this, this is the

00:38:15.570 --> 00:38:16.860
last chapter of my book also.

00:38:16.860 --> 00:38:22.470
Teenagers just decided they're gonna jump
over barbed wire. They're gonna get to this

00:38:22.470 --> 00:38:29.790
place no matter what, and brave the bullets,
and there was obviously a lot of military

00:38:29.790 --> 00:38:38.090
security presence as well. Literally guns
and roses because there are so many diverse

00:38:38.090 --> 00:38:40.260
flowers there but so many guns.

00:38:40.260 --> 00:38:46.480
Yet when the music started, it seemed like
that the sun came out. Everybody was singing,

00:38:46.480 --> 00:38:55.550
dancing, and it, I don't wanna sort of exaggerate
what arts and culture can do. For those two

00:38:55.550 --> 00:39:05.010
hours, a door opened, a door of possibility
opened. And for me it crystallized again that

00:39:05.010 --> 00:39:13.560
if we wanna start making this world better,
safer, we need to communicate with each other.

00:39:13.560 --> 00:39:17.321
And it was probably the most important concert
of my life -- that one, yet.

00:39:17.321 --> 00:39:20.770
[applause]

